{{other people|Ahmad Pasha}}
[[Image:ModernEgypt, Prince Ahmed Rifaat Pasha, PRS 2030 1.JPG|thumb|right|Ahmad Rifaat Pasha, 1825–1858]]
'''Ahmad Rifaat Pasha''' (8 December 1825 – 15 May 1858) was a member of the [[Muhammad Ali Dynasty]] of [[Egypt]]. He was [[heir presumptive]] to [[Sa'id of Egypt|Sa'id Pasha]].

However, in 1858, a special train conveying Ahmad Rifaat Pasha was being carried on a [[car float]] across the Nile at [[Kafr el-Zayyat]].<ref name=Hughes>{{cite book|last=Hughes |first=Hugh |year=1981 |title=Middle East Railways |location=Harrow |publisher=Continental Railway Circle |isbn=0-9503469-7-7 |page=17}}</ref> The train fell off the car float into the river and the prince was drowned.<ref name=Hughes/>

Sa'id outlived Ahmad Rifaat until 1863, when he was succeeded by [[Isma'il Pasha]].

