{{For|the television personality|Bill Doleman}}
'''William "Bill" Dolman''' (Reverend Doctor) was [[coroner|H.M.Coroner]] for the Northern District of London from 1993 to 2007. During his career he held over 8000 [[inquests]], including a "[[suicide by cop]]", the first such case in English legal history.<ref name=haringey>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090125070051/http://www.haringey.gov.uk/index/news_and_events/latest_news/coronerretires.htm |archivedate=January 25, 2009 |url=http://www.haringey.gov.uk/index/news_and_events/latest_news/coronerretires.htm |title="Suicide by cop" coroner retires |website=haringey.gov.uk |author= |date=13 December 2007 |deadurl=yes}}</ref> He is the only Coroner to have been a regular BBC broadcaster,<ref name=haringey/> providing medical advice for 25 years to the 6 million regular listeners of the [[Jimmy Young Show]]. He founded the [[Dolman Best Travel Book Award]] in 2006, the only travel book award in the country (as of its founding), given to the best travel book published during the previous year.

